# Design System (Project Standard)

All new UI must use the shared design tokens and components under `lib/core/theme/` and `lib/core/widgets/`. Do not hardcode hex colors, raw `TextStyle` font choices, or one-off button colors in feature code.

## File structure (`lib/core/theme/`)

| File | Responsibility |
|------|----------------|
| `app_colors.dart` | Semantic palette: primary, secondary, tertiary, neutral, dark steps (`*Dark1`–`*Dark3`), and text-on-surface helpers (`onSurfacePrimary`, `onSurfaceSecondary`, `onAccentFill`). |
| `app_text_styles.dart` | Plus Jakarta Sans via `google_fonts`: `headline` (24sp), `body` (16sp), `label` (12sp), plus `textTheme()` for `ThemeData`. |
| `app_theme.dart` | Default app theme: `AppTheme.dark` (`ThemeData` dark, Material 3, scaffold background `AppColors.neutral`). |
| `app_button_styles.dart` | Reusable `ButtonStyle` factories for the four variants below. |

Reusable field: `lib/core/widgets/app_text_field.dart` (`AppTextField`).

## Color naming convention (`app_colors.dart`)

- **Base tokens:** `primary`, `secondary`, `tertiary`, `neutral` (main background `#0C1324`).
- **Progressive dark accents:** for each base color, `primaryDark1` → `primaryDark3` (same pattern for `secondary*` and `tertiary*`). For `neutral`, `neutralDark1` → `neutralDark3` are progressively darker surfaces.
- **Text helpers:** `onSurfacePrimary`, `onSurfaceSecondary`, `onAccentFill` (label on filled primary/secondary buttons).

## Button style variants (`AppButtonStyles`)

- `primaryFilled()` — filled primary (`AppColors.primary`), dark label (`onAccentFill`).
- `secondaryFilled()` — filled secondary (`AppColors.secondary`), dark label.
- `inverted()` — dark surface, light border, light text (`OutlinedButton`).
- `outlined()` — transparent fill, primary border and primary text.

Use with `FilledButton` / `OutlinedButton` via `style: AppButtonStyles.primaryFilled()`, etc.

## Rules for new UI

- Import and use **`AppColors`** for any color (containers, borders, icons); never scatter `Color(0xFF...)` in views except inside `app_colors.dart`.
- Import and use **`AppTextStyles`** (or `Theme.of(context).textTheme` from `AppTheme`) for typography; do not call `GoogleFonts` or set arbitrary `fontSize`/`fontFamily` in widgets.
- Apply **`AppTheme.dark`** at the app root (`MaterialApp.theme`); extend the theme via `copyWith` only when necessary and prefer tokens.
- Prefer **`AppTextField`** (or theme-aligned `InputDecoration`) for text fields on dark backgrounds.
